   <dcterms:title>Letter, Martha Washington to Hannah Washington, 1784 June 22 </dcterms:title>
   <dcterms:creator>Washington, Martha, 1731-1802</dcterms:creator>
   <dcterms:contributor>Washington, Hannah Bushrod, approximately 1738-1804</dcterms:contributor>
   <dcterms:created>1784-06-22</dcterms:created>
   <dcterms:description>Martha Washington acknowledges that she has received the cotton for spinning from the addressee. Also hopes to visit Mrs. Washington if the General can find time. Intends to send a weeping willow when the season is right. She also congratulates Mrs. Washington on the birth of another child. Autograph letter signed, 3 pages with integral address panel. Partial black wax seal. </dcterms:description>
